bibl.note: Our transcription is based on a digital image of the microfilmed original.

div1.p: In the District Court, Of the Third Judicial District of Washington Territory, holding Terms at Seattle, for the Counties of King and Kitsap.
The People of the United States of America, to the Sheriff George Finleyson of King County Greeting: Greeting:

We command you that you have the body of George Walker John San Francisco and Pedro O'Brien by you imprisioned and detained as it is said together with the time and cause of such imprisonment and detention, by whatsoever name said George Walker John San Francisco and Pedro O'Brien shall be called or charged, before the Hon. Roger S. Greene, Judge of the aforesaid Court at Seattle, in the Court House in said City of the 2nd day of November 1885 at 9 o'clock A.M. to do and receive what shall then and there be considered concerning the said George Walker, John San Francisco and Pedro O Brien And have you then and there this writ.
Witness The Hon. Roger S. Greene, Judge of said District Court, and the seal thereof this 31st day of October A. D. 1885.

James Seavey, Clerk
By James P. Ludlow Deputy
